caption.paragraph:
Fig. 13.
Storenosoma altum . (a–b)
male palp (KS42843): (a) ventral; (b) RTA, retrolateral. (c–d) female genitalia: (c) epigynum, ventral (KS42548); (d) internal (KS42549). Scale lines 0.25 mm.

subSubSection.paragraph: Description . Male . Measurements: BL 6.25, CL 3.50, CW 2.75, PLE 0.33, PME 0.23 (QM, S1384). Female . Measurements: BL 7.85, CL 3.60, CW 2.64, PLE 0.35, PME 0.22 (QM, S1383). For morphological description see species diagnosis and generic description.
Distribution . North eastern New South Wales and south eastern Queensland ( Fig. 27b ).
Remarks . The female holotype has the epigynum plugged.
